column1: # images and their seed count with appropriate H, S, B values for color thresholding
# H_lower, H_upper, S_lower, S_upper, B_lower, B_upper are the lower and upper HSB values
# bulk_sampled refer to samples obtained from entire binary image
# bulk_sampled_total_area is the number of pixels occupied by all objects in binary image
# solo_sampled refer to stats based on object properties obtained after filtering with the pixel size(generally, 400-2000 px^2) that selects for single seeds only
# actual_count is the painstakenly couted total number of grains in whole image
# solo_adjustment is arbitrarily chosen after viewing the histogram distribution

column7: # segmentation only(count, total area, average size, percentage area, mean )
